        <div id="main_instructions" class="row">
            <div class="large-12 columns">
            	<p>This form is for students (Current & Former) and alumni of the University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) to request disciplinary records to be released to themselves or others. This includes, but is not limited to high school prom authorization forms, graduate and professional schools, state bar associations, government agencies, or independent agencies when applying for admission or employment.<br />
<br />
Students (Current & Former) and alumni must provide the following:<br />
<br />
(1) A signed release form providing the University permission to release this information. If you already have a form you have signed as part of your application, please upload it in the <b><span style="color:red;">"Supporting Documentation"</span></b> section. Alternately, please complete the <b><a href="http://go.uic.edu/FERPARelease" target=\"_blank\">Consent Form for Release of Information (FERPA Form)</a></b> and upload it in the <b><span style="color:red;">"Supporting Documentation"</span></b> section.<br />
<br />
(2) Any documents/forms from the institutions to which you want us to send a report; <br />
<br />
(3) Please upload a copy of a photo ID (i.e., State ID or Driver's License) in order to confirm your identity. <br />
<br />
<b>Please allow 5-7 business days for your request to be processed.</b> If you have any questions, please contact the Office of the Dean of Students at 312-996-4857.</p>            </div>
        </div>
